1 Section 3. Section 33-15-1106, MCA, is amended to read:
2 "33-15-1106. Renewal with altered terms. (1) If an insurer offers or purports to renew a policy but on
3 less favorable terms, at a higher rate, or at a higher rating plan, the new terms, rate, or rating plan take effect
4 on the policy renewal date only if the insurer has mailed or delivered notice of the new terms, rate, or rating
5 plan to the insured at least 45 90 days before the expiration date.
6 (2) This section does not apply if the increase in the rate or the rating plan, or both, results from a
7 classification change based on the altered nature or extent of the risk insured against."
8
9 Section 4. Section 33-15-1107, MCA, is amended to read:
10 "33-15-1107. Information about grounds for nonrenewal. (1) If the insurer or insurance producer
11 receives a written request from an insured within 60 business days from the date on which the insurer mailed a
12 notice of cancellation or nonrenewal to the insured, the insurer or insurance producer shall, within 21 days of
13 receiving the insured's written request, The insurer or insurance producer shall furnish the insured the
14 information that the insurer or insurance producer used to make its decision when sending its notice of
15 cancellation or nonrenewal to the insured. A notice is not effective unless it contains adequate information
16 about the insured's right to make the request relating to the insurer's decision to cancel or not renew the policy.
17 An insured may take actions to cure the issues in the nonrenewal notice after receiving the notice. The insurer
18 shall consider the insured's curative actions and the insurer's nonrenewal of the policy.
19 (2) This section does not apply if the ground for cancellation or nonrenewal is nonpayment of the
20 premium and the reason is stated in the notice."
21
22 Section 5. Section 33-23-212, MCA, is amended to read:
23 "33-23-212. Notice required for cancellation -- statement that insurer will specify reason upon
24 request -- exception. (1) A cancellation by an insurer of a motor vehicle liability insurance policy is not
25 effective prior to the mailing or delivery to the named insured, at the address shown in the policy, of a written
26 notice of the cancellation stating the date on which, not less than 45 90 days after the date of the mailing or
27 delivery, the cancellation becomes effective. Other provisions of this code may not be construed as affecting
28 the requirements provided in this subsection (1).
