13 Section 6. Section 33-23-213, MCA, is amended to read:
14 "33-23-213. Notice to insured of ground for cancellation -- commissioner to ensure
15 compliance. (1) Whenever an insurer gives notice of cancellation of a motor vehicle liability policy, upon
16 request of the insured, the insurer, within 15 days of receipt of the request, the insurer shall furnish to the
17 insured a statement setting forth the ground or grounds upon on which the notice of cancellation is based.
18 (2) If the insurer fails to comply with the provisions of this section, the insured may apply to the
19 commissioner for a certificate of the facts or information desired.
20 (3) The commissioner shall exercise any power conferred upon on the commissioner by law that
21 may be necessary to ensure compliance with this section."
